==English==

{{rank|married|slowly|silence|703|afterwards|horses|wonder|smile}}

===Etymology===
AS. æfteweard, a., behind.  See [[Aft]], and [[-ward]] (suffix). The final ''s'' in ''afterwards'' is adverbial, originally a genitive ending.

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ˈæf.tɚ.wɚdz/

===Adverb===
'''afterward''' {{US}} or '''afterwards'''

# At a later or succeeding time.

